&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;first-paragraph&quot;&gt;At Turtle Rock, we make the games we want to play. We&#39;re dedicated to providing a collaborative environment where our team members feel empowered with the creative freedom to contribute and grow. While we are based in Orange County, CA, we support flexible work arrangements ranging from in-studio, hybrid, to fully remote throughout North America. Join our award-winning game development team and help create our next hit title.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Lead VFX Artist to be a part of our VFX team. The Lead VFX Artist will maintain consistency across the department providing direction and feedback, ensuring all team members understand their role in the department and know what is expected of them. The right candidate will look for opportunities to enhance the player experience, embrace and provide constructive feedback while guiding the creative process; driving VFX process for game effects. This position will report to the Creative Director.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the VFX team: maintain consistency across the department providing direction and feedback, ensuring all team members understand their role in the department and know what is expected of them&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead team meetings and relay important studio information when required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with department manager to provide mentorship and coaching for VFX team members including but not limited to: 1:1s, career development, performance evaluations, and goal setting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide the creative process; drive the concept process for game effects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring&amp;nbsp;in-progress&amp;nbsp;and prototype effects to completion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with the Art Directors and art teams to ensure artistic unity across the game&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create real-time visual effects to enhance environments, characters, and combat&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with designers, engineers, and other artists in creating strong moment-to-moment gameplay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with other team members to ensure that assets fall within set parameters in regards to performance, best practices, and art style&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Playtest with both the studio and the VFX team to review and iterate VFX&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years game experience in creating effects&amp;nbsp;in game development with one or more shipped titles on multiple platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong portfolio demonstrating expertise in creating real-time effects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-driven, strong communication skills, and a positive attitude&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to problem-solve and prioritize issues while working with a team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with creating compelling, real-time effects using Photoshop, Maya, and/or in-game effects systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledgeable of 3D graphics, particle systems, physics, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in UE5&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keen production sensibilities, ability to collaborate on timelines and communicate with Production and team members on task duration and prioritization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to maintain high quality and consistent progress&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong leadership, mentoring, and teaching skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong ability to interpret and adapt to general and flexible direction.&amp;nbsp;Can thrive in a highly collaborative, team-oriented environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in Maya, 3ds Max, or Blender&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferences&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shipped one or more major titles on current generation/PC platforms as a Senior VFX artist&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with AAA First Person action

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;first-paragraph&quot;&gt;At Turtle Rock, we make the games we want to play. We&#39;re dedicated to providing a collaborative environment where our team members feel empowered with the creative freedom to contribute and grow. While we are based in Orange County, CA, we support flexible work arrangements ranging from in-studio, hybrid, to fully remote throughout North America. Join our award-winning game development team and help create our next hit title.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a Senior Data Analyst to drive data-informed decision-making across our studio. You&#39;ll be at the intersection of engineering, analytics, and strategy. Working hands-on at all layers of the stack to turn player data into insights that shape the direction of our games and business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the entire data pipeline from instrumentation to presentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work directly with departments and senior leadership to decide what to gather and how to analyze it&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify KPIs around engagement, retention, and churn, and design pipelines to collect them&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the databases: schema, performance, health&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be hands-on with the ETL pipelines and the infrastructure supporting it&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Automate reporting and create dashboards for a variety of audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Play the game&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;styles--2kg4_&quot; data-ui=&quot;job-requirements&quot;&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years in a data analyst or analytics engineering role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong SQL skills: querying, structuring schemas, tuning performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong skills in the languages of your choice for backend and analysis: Python, R, Java, etc&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Real world experience building and owning ETL processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Statistical modeling depth: regression analysis, hypothesis testing, predictive models, confidence and error&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable presenting to technical and non-technical audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-starter energy — you can juggle priorities, work across teams, and figure things out without a lot of hand-holding&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferences&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Games industry experience, especially large multiplayer games&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional background in Unreal and C++&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with a JVM language for backend work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Snowflake or other columnar databases like Redshift&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;styles--21mG1&quot; data-ui=&quot;job-benefits&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some of the benefits and perks our employees get to enjoy, include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;100% Medical, Dental, Vision Coverage for you and your family&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Retirement Savings Plan Matching&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Career Improvement Plan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible Work Arrangements - In-House, Hybrid, and Remote&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous Time Off Policy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Company Events - In-Person + Virtual Events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fully Stocked Kitchen + Sponsored Food Trucks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The estimated base pay range for this role is:&amp;nbsp; USD $100,000 - $140,000&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We are an equal opportunity employer and value diversity at our company. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;first-paragraph&quot;&gt;At Turtle Rock, we make the games we want to play. We&#39;re dedicated to providing a collaborative environment where our team members feel empowered with the creative freedom to contribute and grow. While we are based in Orange County, CA, we support flexible work arrangements ranging from in-studio, hybrid, to fully remote throughout North America. Join our award-winning game development team and help create our next hit title.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;At Turtle Rock, UI/UX is a high-value driver of major features in our games, not just a support function. As a Senior UI Producer, you’re the production hub of all things UX and UI. You are not only the day-to-day planner, runner, and advocate of a cross-functional UI team of designers, engineers, and artists, you are also a key driver in building UI-led features across the wider team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take ownership of high level initiatives and work with all departments to complete goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and maintain the UI roadmap and the UI backlog, ensuring progress or changes are communicated across various channels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In partnership with the UI Design, Art, and Engineering Leads, conduct milestone planning, task and bug prioritizations to ensure the team is working on the right things at the right time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with other Producers to plan and schedule work across teams for features led and supported by UI.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with UI leads and team to create estimated tasks for work and follow the work through its lifecycle, unblocking as needed along the way.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage change requests, both at the stakeholder and team level. Negotiate compromises and propose solutions to get the project’s needs met.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep stakeholders apprised of feature production status (leading regular feature review meetings, weekly team syncs, stakeholder syncs).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and improve team processes (kick-offs, planning, stand ups, triages) to ensure work is asked for, created, and completed in a predictable manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and improve feature pipeline and team workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify production problems, establish facts, and propose solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure meetings are productive, noted, and that actions captured are followed up on.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the reliable, stable source of information, support, and engagement that our team counts on to thrive.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Playtest with the studio and UI team to iterate based on playtest feedback and player experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Requirements&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years experience in the games industry&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 2 years working with larger teams in a cross-functional feature production capacity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert with Jira (Jira Plans experience a plus), Confluence, the Google suite&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert project management skills: resource management, time management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Warm and supportive verbal/written communication skills, even under pressure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient at multitasking and managing competing priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effectively communicate risks and obstacles to both team members and stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Preferences&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shipped at least 1 AAA title&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with teams with timezone deltas of 3 hours +/-&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong passion for playing games&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with contract/outsourcing partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing feedback from test and focus groups&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
